Hon. Uche Okafor of the All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA) has emerged the Speaker of the Anambra State House of Assembly. Okafor, who represents Aghamelum constituency in the state, was elected unopposed by the state lawmakers. Similarly, Hon. Pascal Agbodike, also of APGA, who represents Ohiala II constituency at the state assembly has emerged Deputy Speaker unopposed. Daily Trust reports that the swearing-in is still ongoing as at the time of filing this report. Ogun: Oluomo emerges new speaker Youths make inroads as state assembly speakers emerge Rep Ogene loses APGA ticket to Anambra speaker Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin